<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-098-496  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 098 496.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 27 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Vi-Spy now protects against more than 40 viruses. (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   RG Software Systems Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Vi-Spy 2.0 (Data security software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersData SecurityProduct IntroductionComputer viruses.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>VI-SPY NOW PROTECTS AGAINST MORE THAN 40 VIRUSES WILLOW GROVE, PENNSYLVANIA,U.S.A., 1990 JAN 26 (NB) -- Raymond Glath, developer of Vi-Spy, has announcedthat RG Software will begin shipping Release 2 of Vi-Spy on Monday.andM;The second edition detects and eliminates about twice as many kinds of virusinfections as the initial version and also offers other enhancements.andM;Vi-Spy is a file-checking program which very rapidly checks every executablefile on a single system or even on a complete network and can also be used totest floppy discs.andP;  When an infected file is located, the variety of theparticular virus is reported, and Vi-Spy completely overwrites the file; itdoesn't just delete the file name.andM;Vi-Spy runs under DOS 2.0 or higher, comes on both 5.25- and 3.5-inch disksin a single package, and sells for $250, complete with a tutorial manual tohelp users detect and remove virus infections.andP;  Site licenses are unnecessaryfor corporate or government users who need buy only one copy of Vi-Spy foreach location, but for larger operations, with computers at differentlocations, site license and multiple copy discounts are available.andO;Otherwise, the program is meant to be run from a floppy and used only whenneeded or on a regular basis by the system guru, so only one copy is neededfor each office.andM;Although Vi-Spy is not copy protected, it should not be loaded onto a harddisk as a protection against infection of Vi-Spy and, in any case, it islicensed so that one person, the one in charge of software security, can takeit from machine to machine or run it on a network and test all files.andM;Among the new features in this version is a self-check feature which firsttests Vi-Spy for the presence of a virus and shuts down immediately ifanything is wrong with the files.andP;  There is also a memory check where Vi-Spylooks for any virus already hiding in RAM or random access memory.andM;In addition to checking for executable files containing virus signatures, thelatest edition also looks for virus code in .OV*,  .PGM, and .BIN files.andM;Mr.andP;  Glath, who is a leader in the fight against computer vandalism,expressed satisfaction with the conviction of Robert Morris this Monday,saying that he thought it sent the right message to the industry andpotentially destructive hackers, but he is still concerned that Mr. Morriswill receive too lenient a sentence.andM;Vi-Spy is available from RG Software, Inc., 2300 Computer Ave., Suite E28,Willow Grove, Pa.andP;  19090, U.S.A.andP;  215-659-5300.andP;  An upgrade service costing$150 gives subscribers free updates as new virus programs are detected andincorporated in Vi-Spy.andM;Note: Those who purchase Vi-Spy (and remember to register it) get one freequarterly upgrade.andM;(John McCormick/1990126/Press Contact: Beverly Ann Glath, RG, 215-659-5300)</TEXT></DOC>